name: StudentFreelance.com
overview: StudentFreelance.com keeps jobs in America by insourcing work to students. Before StudentFreelance.com students only had two options. They could take up an internship, which meant a lot of boring busywork, being underappreciated and underpaid (if paid at all), and walking away without gaining the experience desired. Their only other option was to take a minimum wage job that would not help them achieve their career goals. Employers also had their share of problems before StudentFreelance.com. They could spend a ton of money competing over local professionals with larger sized companies that have much bigger pockets, or they could outsource their work to foreign countries where there are language barriers, different time zones, cultural differences, and the quality of work would suffer as a result. StudentFreelance.com directly addresses these problems and solves them by introducing employers to students studying in American schools. With StudentFreelance.com, students can set their work hours, gain relevant experience, and earn an income. Employers gain access to a talented workforce that is cost effective and efficient to scale.

external_links.title: StudentFreelance Pulls Students Away From Boring Studying And Drinking, Sticks Them Into The Real World
